{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_013U6hchGCtURiR1ENyKgkcU","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"All three jobs completed successfully. Here's the full summary:\n\n---\n\n## Results Summary\n\n### Step 1: Diagnosis\nThe cluster came up cleanly — Spark master registered one worker, both pods were `Running`, and the baseline job started without configuration errors. No bugs needed to be fixed in this deployment.\n\n### Step 2: Baseline Performance (no optimization)\n- **Skew ratio: 44x** (max partition: 11,579 rows, min: 263 rows)\n- **Elapsed: 27.6s**\n- Hot products (id 1–5) received ~50% of all orders, causing severe shuffle imbalance\n\n### Step 3: Broadcast Join Optimization\n- **Elapsed: 14.6s** — **1.9x faster than baseline**\n- Eliminates the skewed shuffle by broadcasting the small `products` table to all executors\n- No shuffle needed → no straggler partitions\n\n### Step 4: AQE (Adaptive Query Execution) Optimization\n- **Elapsed: 11.7s** — **2.4x faster than baseline**\n- Spark detects skewed partitions at runtime and auto-splits hot partitions\n- `spark.sql.adaptive.skewJoin.enabled=true` with a 1-byte threshold forces splitting\n\n### Performance Comparison\n\n| Strategy | Elapsed | Speedup | Method |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| Baseline | 27.6s | 1.0x | Skewed shuffle join (44x partition imbalance) |\n| Broadcast Join | 14.6s | **1.9x** | Broadcasts small table, avoids shuffle entirely |\n| AQE Skew Join | 11.7s | **2.4x** | Auto-splits hot partitions at runtime |\n\n**AQE wins** for this workload — it handles the skew dynamically without requiring you to know which table is small enough to broadcast. Both optimization strategies significantly outperform the baseline with the severe 44x data skew."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":170,"cache_read_input_tokens":44166,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_token